thread.title: Texas Tech disappointed with next-to-last possession against TCU
thread.title_full: Texas Tech disappointed with next-to-last possession against TCU | Dallas Morning News

author: Chuck Carlton
title: Texas Tech disappointed with next-to-last possession against TCU
text:
LUBBOCK - Tech coaches and players were unhappy with their next-to-last possession.
The Red Raiders gained possession with 4:44 left and leading 52-48. But a chance to build the lead or at least kill the lock ended with a three-and-out.
"We didn't put pressure on them to keep the clock going," said running back DeAndre Washington, who ran for a career-high 188 yards on 22 carries and fourth touchdowns. "You know, we've got to execute that better."
